                                            <p>
                                        Dr. Maheswar Rupakheti is an atmospheric scientist with a strong focus on air quality, climate change, and the science-policy-society interface, particularly in the Himalayan region. He currently serves as Vice-Chair of Working Group I of the IPCC Bureau and leads the research group "Regional Air Quality and Climate in Southern Asia" at the 
